Cling Attack			TYPE:Combat																PRESIZELTEQ:T																					DESC:You attach yourself to larger enemies allowing you to attack up close and personal.								SOURCEPAGE:pg.11		BENEFIT:If you share the space of a creature Medium-sized or larger, you can make a special Combat Maneuver check with a +8 bonus to hold onto the surface of the creature. Once attached you lose any Dexterity bonus to your AC, as does your opponent against your attacks. It takes a move action to maintain the hold, but you can still use standard actions normally. You must succeed on a concentration check to cast a spell or use a spell-like ability while clinging. Opponents can only attack you with one-handed weapons or attempt to remove you with a grapple. You receive a +8 bonus to your Combat Maneuver Defense against the grapple check.
Companion Aid			TYPE:General																																						DESC:Your companion creature helps you more than is typical.												SOURCEPAGE:pg.12		BENEFIT:When flanking or aiding another, your animal companion or familiar grants you a +4 bonus.
Companion Friend			TYPE:General																																						DESC:You've become adept at working with willful companions.												SOURCEPAGE:pg.12		BENEFIT:You get a +4 bonus to Diplomacy or Intimidate checks to convince a willful companion to do something it does not want to do.
Drake Dart				TYPE:Combat				PREFEAT:1,Dodge													PRESKILL:1,Acrobatics=2																	DESC:By imitating a drake's quickness, you give yourself a better chance to avoid attacks of opportunity provoked by movement.	SOURCEPAGE:pg.12		BENEFIT:In place of your armor class, you may make an Acrobatics check to set the DC for an attack of opportunity against you.
Ease of Form			TYPE:General																									PRETEXT:Ability to shapechange into two different types of creatures.	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:USERINPUT|TITLE=Creature Form	SELECT:1	DESC:You are comfortable changing shape into a favorite creature.												SOURCEPAGE:pg.12		BENEFIT:When changing into your creature shapes, treat the duration as if modified by the Extend Spell feat. This includes any change to spell level and other variables. This feat may be chosen multiple times. Each time it is chosen, it applies to a different form. The benefits of this feat do not stack with Extend Spell.
Exceptional Relationship	TYPE:General			PREFEAT:1,Willful Companion Drake		PREPCLEVEL:MIN=11										PRESTAT:1,CHA=15														DESC:You and your drake companion share a stronger bond.												SOURCEPAGE:pg.12	BENEFIT:Your drake companion can serve as an animal companion or improved familiar if you have access to those abilities. While you still must spend 1 gp per HD per day on your companion drake, you no longer need to make Diplomacy checks as the two of you have built a bond of trust.
Foe Climb				TYPE:Combat				PREFEAT:3,Cling Attack,Dodge,Mobility						PRESIZELTEQ:T																					DESC:You can scale larger opponents.								SOURCEPAGE:pg.12		BENEFIT:When you make a successful Cling Attack against a Medium or larger opponent, you retain your Dexterity bonus to AC and you need not spend a move action to maintain your grip, allowing you to use full-round actions.
